Junk DB

A simple database to store scripts states


Databases are automatically created when they are first accessed.
A database is composed of a unique state and a generic data list.
Data cannot be accessed directly, and can only be checked for equality, added, or removed.


protocol:

<db-name> <ACTION> <payload>


actions:

IS,     check if unique state equals payload

SET,    set unique state to payload

HAS,    check if database contains payload

ADD,    add payload to database

REM,    remove payload from database
